        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Heh. Interesting to see we all have a different logic.</P><P>I always use /boo instead of book. I assume y'all do that too.</P><P>/boo 0/1 - Often used Utility (Gate, Levant, Gather, ITU..)<BR>/boo 2/3 - Standby Utility (Conjure Corpse, Convergenc, Sacrifice..)<BR>/boo 4/5 - Page 4 Self Buffs, Page 5 DD<BR>/boo 6/7 - Page 6 fast Dots, Page 7 slow dots<BR>/boo 8/9 - PRIMARY set (Lich, Vex, Shadowb, Doom, Fear, Twitch, Scream)<BR>/boo 10/11 - Page 10 Group Util (DMF, Annul..), Page 11 Roots<BR>/boo 12/13 - Page 12 Pets, Page 13 Pet+Util (summon, augment, reclaim)<BR>/boo 14/15 - Page 14 Undead, Page 15 other (defol, low lvl snare, fear)<BR>/boo 16/17 - <BR>/boo 18/19 - Page 18 (cascading, low fears) Page 19 Debuffs</P><P>All outdates spells fill pages 25+, sorted by type and level. (spells, liches, buffs, debuffs, dots)</P><P>I could be more specific than that.. but all this is from memory. I tend to not use hotkeys to flip pages, as usually those are set up for /assist MA, /target cleric, /target enchanter, pet back off, pet attack, mezz announce, etc. I have no room, and don't want to deal with the Shift+2 crap unless I have to. (they're set up, quick pages 8 and 9 are spellbook locations, I just never use them.)</P><P>I use /boo 9 as my primary, because I wanted my PRIMARY spells to be within a page flip away from spells I use commonly. Reason is, when I do spell swaps, I'm usually swapping MORE than one spell.</P><P>Like in HS, I may need to /boo 15, unmemm 2 dots, memm thrall and screaming. Stand up, deal with the undead, then /boo 9 and remem my lich, and flip back a page to remem the two dots.</P><P>Also, I've learned to click the spell on the spellbook FIRST, _before_ unmemming the spell gem. I learned early on that if I unmem root, or screaming, fear, or even FD before I select the spell I'm replacing it with, and I get hit, casted, on, go LD, etc... then I might be in some trouble.</P><P>By clicking the spell first, then right-clicking and removing the current spell, I at least have a tiny insurance I still have some spells to work with if something happens.</P><P><center><img src="http://www.havocink.com/eq/malys_siggy.gif" border=0></center><BR>____________________<BR><font size=1><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61374" target="_blank">Malys Undying</a> | House Archon</font id=size1><BR>57 Necromancers in One</font></td>
      </tr>
